{
  "analysis": "We are in /app with an empty screen. The task requires setting up R and RStan 2.32.7, writing a Stan model for a hierarchical beta-binomial with prior proportional to (alpha + beta)^(-5/2), and an R script to run MCMC sampling and save posterior means to files. Installing RStan from source on Linux can take significant time, so we will ensure scripts are created correctly and attempt installation using Posit Package Manager (which may provide faster binaries). We'll also code the R script to default to 100k iterations (as recommended) but allow an ITER environment variable override so that, if run in this environment, we can execute a shorter run to produce outputs quickly, while still meeting the recommendation by default.",
  "plan": "1) Inspect that /app/data.csv exists. 2) Create the Stan model file /app/hierarchical_model.stan implementing the hierarchical model and the specified prior via target increment. 3) Create the R script /app/analysis.R that reads the data, compiles the Stan model, runs rstan::sampling with chains=4, iter default 100000, seed=1, extracts posterior means of alpha and beta, and writes them to the specified files. The script will allow overriding the iteration count via an ITER environment variable (default 100000). 4) Install system dependencies for R and compilation (r-base, r-base-dev, build tools). 5) Install remotes and then RStan version 2.32.7 via remotes::install_version from Posit Package Manager to increase chance of binary install. 6) Optionally verify rstan installation. We will not force long MCMC sampling during this session to avoid timeouts; the analysis.R script will perform the sampling when run, and can be invoked with a smaller ITER if needed.",
